This changes the semantics of our notification registration. We now only hold weak references to notifications, so users must hold onto a reference for notifications to stay valid. The upside of this is that to unregister a notification, you just have to nullify your reference.

We also now allow you to pass an optional context to a notification, which eliminates the need to cast to weak variables when accessing controller properties/variables.

